<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="1155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1155">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/62b</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2945. There is a strong feeling here of sympathy for the destitute in
                                Poland, and an increasing demand that relief should be sent to them.
                                To all inquiries Department advises that <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> is now endeavoring to secure the necessary
                                permission to extend over Poland organization of the Belgian Relief
                                Commission, and that when this is accomplished, as it is hoped it
                                will be, relief can go forward from this country. If you see no
                                objection, you may advise <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward
                                    Grey</persName> of the anxiety of large numbers of American
                                citizens and of their desire to send assistance to the destitute in
                                Poland. See Department’s 2926, 23d, and inform <persName corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> prompt reply requested.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>